# UI Annotations ("UI comments")

When the user asks for "UI comments" or "annotate the UI", use this pattern: numbered badges overlaid on images with matching numbered comments in a side panel.

## Structure

```tsx
{(() => {
  // ── Edit annotations here ──────────────────────────────
  const annotations: { id: number; text: string }[] = [
    { id: 1, text: "Your comment for element 1" },
    { id: 2, text: "Your comment for element 2" },
  ];
  // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  const Badge = ({ n }: { n: number }) => (
    <span
      className="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full select-none flex-shrink-0"
      style={{ width: 24, height: 24, backgroundColor: "#1B1917", color: "#F4F2EF", fontSize: 12, fontWeight: 600, lineHeight: 1 }}
    >
      {n}
    </span>
  );

  return (
    <div className="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_280px] gap-12 items-start">
      {/* Images with badges */}
      <div className="relative flex-shrink-0">
        <img src="/your-image.png" alt="..." className="w-full h-auto" />
        {/* Position badge with top/left as percentages */}
        <span className="absolute" style={{ top: "10%", left: "5%" }}>
          <Badge n={1} />
        </span>
      </div>

      {/* Comment list */}
      <ul className="space-y-5 list-none pt-2">
        {annotations.map((a) => (
          <li key={a.id} className="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span className="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><Badge n={a.id} /></span>
            <p className="body text-text-default">{a.text}</p>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>
  );
})()}
```

## Rules
- Always use inline styles for the Badge (not Jøkul typography classes — they break the circle rendering)
- Image wrappers must be `relative` for badge positioning
- Position badges with `style={{ top: "X%", left: "X%" }}` using percentages so they scale with the image
- The annotation list lives in a `280px` right column
- Multiple images can share the same annotation list — just stack them in the left column
